<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - MediTrack</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <script defer src="script.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>MediTrack Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> February 2025</p>

        <div class="policy-content">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>At MediTrack, we prioritize your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when you use our medication management platform.</p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details (name, email, phone number).</li>
                <li>Medication records and adherence history.</li>
                <li>Device and usage data for improving service quality.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide medication tracking and reminders.</li>
                <li>To allow caregivers to monitor adherence.</li>
                <li>To enhance platform security and performance.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We use encryption and secure storage methods to protect user data. MediTrack does not share your data with third parties without your consent.</p>

            <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information. Contact our support team for any data-related requests.</p>

            <h2>6. Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update our privacy policy periodically. Continued use of MediTrack after updates means acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-footer">
            <input type="checkbox" id="acceptPrivacy">
            <label for="acceptPrivacy">I acknowledge the Privacy Policy</label>
            <button id="proceedBtn" disabled>Proceed</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
